This mineral is employed in many ways:—the coarser varieties, when burnt to drive
                    off the carbonic acid, as lime, for mortar, manure, tanning; as a flux in
                    melting iron and other ores, or in preparing glass, and for similar purposes;
                    the finer, as marbles, for sculpture, architecture, and ornamental stone-work;
                    the chalk for writing, whitewashing, or producing carbonic acid.

